-- ── Gorgias ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Gorgias is an ecommerce-focused customer service helpdesk and AI agent platform that unifies email, chat, social, voice and SMS support with deep Shopify integration.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Subscription$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$$10/month (Starter plan, 50 tickets)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2015, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$500+ employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Francisco, California, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$French$q$, $q$Spanish$q$, $q$German$q$, $q$Portuguese$q$, $q$Italian$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Gorgias Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Gorgias review for 2026 covering its ecommerce helpdesk, AI Agent, Shopify integration, pricing tiers from Starter to Enterprise, pros, cons and alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Gorgias is a customer service helpdesk and conversational AI platform purpose-built for ecommerce brands, unifying support conversations from email, live chat, social media, voice and SMS into a single agent workspace while giving both human agents and an integrated AI Agent direct access to store data such as orders, customer profiles, refunds and product catalogs. Rather than being a general-purpose helpdesk retrofitted for online retail, Gorgias was designed from the outset around the specific workflows of ecommerce support, such as looking up an order, issuing a refund, or updating a shipping address, all without an agent needing to leave the helpdesk interface or switch into a separate ecommerce admin panel. The company was founded in 2015 by Romain Lapeyre and Alex Plugaru, and it is headquartered in San Francisco, California, having grown from a two-person founding team into an organization with roughly 500 employees spread across offices in San Francisco, New York, Charlotte, Toronto, Buenos Aires, Paris, Lisbon and Sydney as of 2026. Gorgias has raised more than 100 million dollars in venture funding across multiple rounds. Its most prominent round was a 30 million dollar Series C announced in August 2022, led by Transpose Platform and Shopify itself, with participation from investors including CRV, Alven, and individuals such as SaaStr founder Jason Lemkin and Sapphire Ventures partner Rajeev Dham; that round valued the company at approximately 710 million dollars and brought its total funding at the time to roughly 72 million dollars, with subsequent reporting placing cumulative funding above the 100 million dollar mark. Shopify's direct participation as an investor reflects Gorgias's especially close relationship with the ecommerce platform, where Gorgias holds Shopify Premier Partner status for customer experience and reports that roughly 40 percent of Shopify brands using a helpdesk use Gorgias. Technically, Gorgias centers on a unified inbox that pulls in conversations from email, live chat widgets embedded on a merchant's storefront, Instagram and Facebook messages and comments, voice calls, and SMS, all routed into one shared workspace where human agents can see full customer and order context alongside each conversation. Layered on top of the helpdesk is Gorgias's AI Agent, which performs two distinct jobs: a Support Agent role that resolves common post-purchase questions such as order tracking, returns and refund requests, and a Shopping Assistant role that engages pre-purchase site visitors with product recommendations and discount offers to help convert browsing into sales. The AI Agent draws on a merchant's help center articles, website content, uploaded documents and live Shopify data, including order history, product catalogs, inventory levels and customer tags, to generate responses that are accurate and on-brand, and it can take direct action rather than only answering questions, such as editing subscriptions, issuing refunds or updating shipping details across more than 100 connected ecommerce tools. The AI Agent supports replies in more than 80 languages, even when a merchant's own knowledge base is only written in one language, and includes a vision capability that lets it interpret images customers share, such as photos of a damaged item or a screenshot of a receipt. Gorgias integrates most deeply with Shopify but also supports other ecommerce platforms such as BigCommerce, Magento and WooCommerce, along with broader integrations across marketing, loyalty, reviews and subscription-management tools commonly used by online retailers. Gorgias prices its plans around billable ticket volume rather than the number of seats or agents, a deliberate positioning choice the company markets heavily, since the subscription cost stays the same whether a team has five agents or five hundred. As of 2026, Gorgias offers five plans. The Starter plan costs 10 dollars per month and includes 50 billable tickets, with overage billed at 40 cents per additional ticket, aimed at very small stores testing the platform. The Basic plan costs 60 dollars per month on monthly billing, or 50 dollars per month if billed annually, and includes 300 billable tickets, with overages billed at roughly 40 dollars per additional 100 tickets. The Pro plan costs 360 dollars per month on monthly billing, or 300 dollars per month billed annually, and includes 2,000 billable tickets, with overage priced around 36 dollars per additional 100 tickets. The Advanced plan costs 900 dollars per month on monthly billing, or 750 dollars per month billed annually, with a similar overage structure and a higher automation ceiling. At the top, an Enterprise plan is available on a custom quote for the largest merchants needing higher ticket volumes, advanced security, dedicated support and custom contract terms. The AI Agent itself is included on every plan tier, and Gorgias's pricing model charges for AI Agent usage based on successful conversation resolutions rather than bundling an unlimited allotment into the base subscription, meaning AI resolution costs scale separately from the base ticket-volume plan price. Optional Voice and SMS channels carry additional usage-based pricing that scales with call and text volume. Gorgias's target audience is squarely direct-to-consumer and ecommerce brands, ranging from small independent Shopify stores on the Starter or Basic plan to larger, high-volume DTC brands and multi-brand retailers on Pro, Advanced or Enterprise plans that need to manage thousands of monthly support conversations with a mix of human agents and AI automation. Marketing and customer experience teams within these brands are typically the primary users, valuing the platform's ability to turn support interactions into revenue opportunities through the Shopping Assistant's proactive product recommendations, in addition to its core function of resolving support tickets efficiently. Competitively, Gorgias sits in a customer support software category alongside Zendesk, Freshdesk, Help Scout and Intercom, most of which serve a much broader range of industries beyond ecommerce. Gorgias differentiates itself through its ecommerce-native design, its official Shopify Premier Partner status and correspondingly deep, real-time Shopify data integration, its ticket-volume-based rather than per-agent pricing model, and its dual-purpose AI Agent that handles both support resolution and pre-purchase sales assistance rather than support alone. Some customers report that Gorgias's ticket-based pricing and separate AI resolution charges can make total costs less predictable at high volume compared to flatter per-agent pricing models used by some competitors, and organizations outside of ecommerce, or those needing extremely deep customization for complex B2B support workflows, may find more general-purpose platforms like Zendesk better suited to their needs. For ecommerce brands, particularly those on Shopify, Gorgias's tight product-data integration and combined support-plus-sales AI positioning are generally considered its strongest competitive advantages.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '421bda78-e5b8-4973-86a7-1481632d297e';

